# Incident Report - SOC127 SQL Injection Detected

## Alert Information

* Event ID: 235
* Rule: SOC127 - SQL Injection Detected
* Event Time: Mar 07, 2024 12:51 PM
* Source IP: 118.194.247.28
* Destination IP: 172.16.20.12
* Destination Host: WebServer1000

## Investigation Summary

The alert was triggered due to a malicious HTTP request targeting the web server. Analysis of the request URL revealed multiple SQL Injection techniques including UNION SELECT statements, access attempts to information_schema tables, and an attempt to execute system commands through xp_cmdshell.

Further investigation of the web server logs identified the User-Agent string "sqlmap/1.7.2", indicating the use of an automated SQL Injection exploitation tool.

The source IP first accessed the website using a standard web browser and shortly afterward launched automated SQL Injection attempts against the application.

## Evidence

* SQL Injection payload detected.
* UNION SELECT statement observed.
* Attempted access to information_schema.
* Attempted use of xp_cmdshell.
* User-Agent identified as sqlmap/1.7.2.
* Request reached the target web server and received HTTP 200 response.
* Traffic originated from external source IP 118.194.247.28 targeting internal web server 172.16.20.12.

## Impact Assessment

No direct evidence was found confirming successful exploitation or data extraction. However, the activity represents a confirmed malicious SQL Injection attempt against the web application.

## Classification

* Web Attack
* SQL Injection Attempt

## Verdict

True Positive

## Escalation

Escalation to Tier 2 is recommended to determine whether the attack resulted in unauthorized database access, command execution, or data exposure.
